    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Make a melee tech attack against a target you touch. On a miss, this power ends. On a hit, you deal [[/r 2d6]] kinetic damage as you plant an explosive charge on the target's body. You can then detonate the charge as a bonus action, which ends this power. It deals [[/r 1d8]] fire damage if detonated on the same turn. It deals [[/r 2d8]] fire damage on your next turn, increasing by [[/r 1d8]] for each round you do not detonate it, to a maximum of [[/r 6d8]]. If this power ends before you detonate the charge, the target takes no fire damage.</p>\n<p>A creature affected by this power can use an action to attempt to remove the detonator from its person, making a Strength or Dexterity check (the creature chooses the ability to use) against your tech save DC. On a success, this power ends, as the detonator deactivates harmlessly.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Overcharge Tech.</em></strong> When you cast this power using a tech slot of 2nd level or higher, the kinetic damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
